<section class="about-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 style="font-size: clamp(20px, 8vw, 48px); margin-bottom: 16px; white-space: nowrap;">About PostureTru</h1>
    <p style="font-size: clamp(11px, 3.5vw, 18px); color: var(--color-text-secondary); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; white-space: nowrap;">
      A posture awareness trainer, not another brace.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Brand Story -->
<section class="section-padding">
  <div class="container about-section">
    <div class="about-content">
      <h2>Where It Started</h2>
      <p>PostureTru began with a simple observation. Most people don't notice when their posture breaks down. It happens quietly, over long hours of focused work, study, or screen time.</p>
      <p>We didn't want to create another posture brace. Braces rely on restriction, and restriction rarely leads to lasting change. Once they come off, old habits return.</p>
      <p>Instead, we focused on something more fundamental. Awareness.</p>
      <p>PostureTru is designed to help you notice the exact moment your posture begins to shift, so you can correct it in real time. Not by force, but by awareness.</p>
      <p>Over time, those small moments begin to reshape how you carry yourself throughout the day.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="about-img-frame">
      <!-- SVG depicting posture shift before and after -->
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="#F8FAF9" rx="12"/>
        <!-- Before silhouette (red/slouched) -->
        <g opacity="0.4">
          <path d="M120,80 Q105,150 70,220 L130,220 Q145,150 140,80 Z" fill="#E8D8CD"/>
          <circle cx="118" cy="80" r="18" fill="#E8D8CD"/>
          <path d="M120,130 Q80,170 100,210" fill="none" stroke="#C0392B" stroke-width="4"/>
          <text x="110" y="250" font-family="Outfit" font-size="14" fill="#C0392B" text-anchor="middle">Before</text>
        </g>

        <!-- Action Arrow -->
        <path d="M180,150 L220,150 M210,140 L220,150 L210,160" stroke="#1B4965" stroke-width="3" fill="none"/>

        <!-- After silhouette (green/straight) -->
        <g>
          <path d="M280,80 Q280,150 280,220 L340,220 Q340,150 340,80 Z" fill="#E8D8CD"/>
          <circle cx="310" cy="80" r="18" fill="#E8D8CD"/>
          <path d="M310,120 L310,210" stroke="#5FB878" stroke-width="4"/>
          <!-- Active corrector indicator -->
          <rect x="295" y="135" width="30" height="40" fill="#1B4965" rx="3"/>
          <circle cx="310" cy="155" r="4" fill="#5FB878"/>
          <text x="310" y="250" font-family="Outfit" font-size="14" fill="#5FB878" text-anchor="middle">With PostureTru</text>
        </g>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Mission Statement -->
<section class="section-padding" style="background-color: var(--color-bg-light); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);">
  <div class="container about-section">
    <div class="about-img-frame" style="background: var(--color-white);">
      <!-- SVG representing desk health -->
      <svg viewBox="0 0 400 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="#FFFFFF" rx="12"/>
        <rect x="80" y="200" width="240" height="15" fill="#2C3E50" rx="3"/>
        <rect x="190" y="215" width="20" height="50" fill="#7F8C8D"/>
        <rect x="150" y="265" width="100" height="8" fill="#7F8C8D" rx="4"/>
        <rect x="230" y="80" width="70" height="90" rx="6" fill="#F0F4F8" stroke="#E8ECEB" stroke-width="2"/>
        <line x1="245" y1="100" x2="285" y2="100" stroke="#1B4965" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        <line x1="245" y1="120" x2="275" y2="120" stroke="#1B4965" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        <line x1="245" y1="140" x2="280" y2="140" stroke="#1B4965" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        <!-- Shield overlapping -->
        <circle cx="200" cy="150" r="35" fill="#5FB878"/>
        <path d="M190,148 L197,155 L212,142" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" fill="none"/>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="about-content">
      <h2>Our Mission</h2>
      <p>Modern work has made long hours at a desk unavoidable, but awareness of posture is often lost in the process.</p>
      <p>Most existing solutions feel uncomfortable, overly restrictive, or disconnected from real daily use. We built PostureTru to change that.</p>
      <p>Our mission is to make posture awareness simple, comfortable, and accessible for anyone who spends long hours sitting.</p>
      <p>We believe everyone should have access to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A comfortable way to stay aware of posture during the day</li>
        <li>A thoughtfully designed wellness tool that fits naturally into daily life</li>
        <li>A product experience that feels supportive, not restrictive</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: 20px;">We are not a large health corporation. We are people who understand what it feels like to sit for hours at a desk and slowly lose track of how your body feels.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Why Choose Us -->
<section class="section-padding" style="background-color: var(--color-bg);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <h2>Why Choose PostureTru</h2>
      <p style="white-space: nowrap; font-size: clamp(12px, 3.2vw, 18px);">Awareness leads to change more naturally than correction.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-3">
      <!-- Col 1 -->
      <div class="pillar-card" style="text-align: center;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Built for Remote Work</h3>
        <p>We understand long hours at a desk because we live them too. PostureTru is designed for the realities of remote work, study sessions, and screen focused routines where posture naturally declines over time.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Col 2 -->
      <div class="pillar-card" style="text-align: center;">
        <h3 style="font-size: clamp(12px, 3.5vw, 20px); margin-bottom: 12px; white-space: nowrap;">Premium Quality, Fair Price</h3>
        <p>By keeping production direct and intentional, we focus on quality without unnecessary markup. PostureTru uses soft food grade silicone, durable ABS components, and a precision motion sensor designed for consistent everyday use.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Col 3 -->
      <div class="pillar-card" style="text-align: center;">
        <h3 style="font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px;">Designed Around Awareness</h3>
        <p>At its core, PostureTru uses real time motion sensing to detect when your posture begins to change. Instead of forcing correction, it delivers a subtle reminder that brings your attention back to your body, so better posture becomes something you naturally return to throughout the day.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

